(838, 'TEST HEADING', '<p>There are multiple employment and work experience options available for international students. However, what you can do will depend on your current visa type and education level. This section explains whether you can be employed in the UK with your current visa. Before moving on to the next section, please read this section carefully to understand what you can and cannot do.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you are on a Student Visa:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you will be able to work and, if so, for how long&nbsp;will be stated on your BRP card, and you must strictly adhere to it. Normally, you can work part-time for a maximum of 20 hours per week&nbsp;<u>during</u>&nbsp;your term time. There is no restriction on working hours&nbsp;<u>outside</u>&nbsp;your term time&nbsp;(ie. during vacations), meaning you can do insight programmes, internships, placements or other full-time, non-permanent jobs as long as your visa can cover the employment duration. To work on a permanent job, you will need to have other permissions that allow you to do so.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Term-time timetables are published by your school or university. For more information on term-time&nbsp;arrangements, please visit your university&rsquo;s website or speak to a student support officer.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you are on a Graduate Visa:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There is no restriction on the hours you can work or the type of work you can do before your Graduate Visa expires. A Graduate visa lasts for 2 years. If you have a PhD or other doctoral qualification, it will last for 3 years. You cannot extend your graduate visa&nbsp;beyond the given time limit.&nbsp;You also cannot work as a professional sportsperson, which includes a sports coach, a doctor or a dentist in training.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information about the Graduate Visa, please click here.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you are on a Child Student Visa and 16 or over:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can work part-time during the term for up to 10 hours per week and full-time during vacations. You can also do a work placement as part of your course (but not for more than 50% of your course).</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you are on a Short Study Visa:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You cannot work.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you are on a Dependent Visa:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can work full-time without restriction while your dependent visa is valid. However, you cannot work as a professional sportsperson, which includes a sports coach. You also cannot work as a doctor or dentist in training if your depended visa was granted prior to 5 October 2020 (unless you have a degree in medicine or dentistry from a UK institution or have previously been granted a UK visa that did not restrict their employment as a doctor or dentist in training and were employed as such during that period).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For detailed employment options available for you, please read the following sections by selecting your current education level.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 'career_options_7', 1, 'eng'),
