(1, 'Katherine Cartagena', 'Founder & CEO', 1, '<p>Katherine is a visionary real estate entrepreneur responsible to source, structure and negotiate opportunities while engaging in the underwriting, due diligence and asset management procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Formerly, Katherine worked in investment banking focusing in arranging debt and equity for commercial real estate transactions. In 2011, Katherine spearheaded a private equity real estate expansion division in Latin America for investments opportunities in Colombia and Panama.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Katherine graduated Suma Cum Laude from New York University ( NYU) with a Masters in Real Estate Finance and Investment. Katherine was a semifinalist in the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) Real Estate Case Competition 2016 while representing NYU. Katherine was awarded two scholarships: The Association of Real Estate Women Scholarship and New York Women in Real Estate, WX Scholarship.</p>\r\n', 'image_1650975103_5425.png'),
(2, 'Stephanie Grandelli', 'Asset & Project Manager', 1, '<p>Stephanie has been involved in a variety of assignments ranging from ground-up new construction projects to historical renovations and restorations the New York City and outer boroughs. Stephanie has gained well- rounded experience in a range of construction project applications over her career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stephanie excels in managing projects from the early stages of pre-construction, conceptual design through planning and project completion. Stephanie works together with clients, design professionals and project-related personnel on coordination, scheduling, and implementation of the project details in order to build a successful project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stephanie holds a Bachelor of Science in Political Science from the George Washington University and Master Degreee Real Estate Development at New York University (NYU).</p>\r\n', 'image_1650975127_9122.png'),
(3, 'Daniel Francess', 'Advisor', 1, '<p>Daniel is an entrepreneur and real estate investor with experience in identifying, buying and selling select real estate assets across Hudson County. As a founder and Managing Director of Francess Investment Company, he is instrumental in obtaining financing, financial engineering, deal structuring, sourcing and acquiring real property as well as asset management. He has participated in over 170 complex real estate related transactions throughout his career. He has extensive experience across a multitude of asset classes within the real estate category including multifamily, retail, office, hotel, development land, and industrial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to founding Francess Investment Company, he was working on institutional real estate acquisitions for a top ranked real estate private equity fund. He has also worked as a commercial and residential real estate broker and holds a Masters Degree from NYU in Real Estate.</p>\r\n', 'image_1650975165_3039.png'),
(4, 'Daniel Yaghoubi', 'Advisor', 1, '<p>Founded popbar in 2009. A gourmet gelato shop that opened 40 stores in 8 years. Daniel was integral to the leading the companies growth in franchising, branding and building out all stores.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting in 2017, He expanded his expertise in construction and branding in to real estate development. Leading the ground up construction of over 100 luxury apartments in Brooklyn, NY.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Daniel is in charge of everything from closings, to architect drawings, financing to a finished building, as well as management services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2021, Daniel started investing in industrial real estate in out of state markets and is continuing to grow through 2022.</p>\r\n', 'image_1650975186_5221.png');

